    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of slender, flat, wingless insect with three tail bristles and covered with silvery scales. It normally lives indoors, eating materials containing high percentages of starch, including paste, bookbindings, and wallpaper, causing damage to books and fabrics.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
